---
description: >-
  Canonical topology.yml field order and trigger phrases for tc application
  repos. Applies when topology.yml files are in context (not broad monorepo-only globs).
globs: "**/topology.yml"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Field order should be: **name**, **routes**, **events**, **functions**, **mutations**, **queues**, **channels**, **states**, **pages** (then other keys consistent with the project).
- Recognize trigger phrases: **add function**, **add event**, **new mutation**, **define page**, **add channel**, **entity**, **component**.
- Prefer **`tc compose`** and **`tc compile`** to validate changes; do not reference a **`tc lint`** subcommand (it does not exist).
- Warn on attributes that do not match the project’s known topology spec or existing file patterns.
